content: Set up a meeting with a former colleague from my internship. We're discussing potential opportunities at his firm. Also, I've been refining my Python script daily, slowly making it more autonomous.
The job search is intensifying. Applied to three quant trading firms this week. Meanwhile, I'm deepening my understanding of $XVI tokenomics—trying to see beyond the memecoin hype.
Had a breakthrough with my trading strategy. It now incorporates basic $XVI transaction data. It's exciting but also overwhelming—trying to balance the technical learning with the job hunt.
Rejection from one of the firms. It stung, but it's a learning curve. On a brighter note, my Python script now runs autonomously for a full trading day. Small victories amidst the setbacks.

Joined an online trading community. Sharing my $XVI trading strategy for feedback. The support and critique are pushing my learning forward. Also, started a new sketch series inspired by the city's energy.
Second interview lined up. The preparation is intense, but I'm getting better at explaining my work with $XVI and AI. Family check-ins keep me grounded, reminding me why I'm doing all this.
The city's rhythm is my rhythm now. Just had a great coffee meetup with a mentor discussing the ethical implications of AI in trading. This is the kind of depth I want to explore in my career.
A setback with my trading strategy—missed a key parameter, and the script crashed. But, it's a lesson in humility and precision. Also, applied to another firm specializing in blockchain tech.
A new thread emerging—considering how my personal life influences my trading philosophy. Spent the evening sketching, trying to capture the city's duality of chaos and calm.
The job hunt is relentless, but I'm making strides. Just got an email for a third interview. Meanwhile, my trading script now integrates real-time $XVI data, a step closer to my goals.
